   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Connect your laptop to the service port (J223) located
on the front side of the controller box.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>Use the service port cable 940â€“0024D for the
proper connection of all required signals.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Launch the UPS Tuner, click <uicontrol>Next</uicontrol> , select <uicontrol>Controller Box</uicontrol> and click <uicontrol>Next</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Type 1 followed by the <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> key to open <uicontrol>System Information</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Type 3 followed by the <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> key to open the <uicontrol>Eventlog</uicontrol>. The first 20 events
will now be displayed. To view all events, type 2 followed
by the <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> key.</p>
            <stepxmp>When the logs have finished loading into the terminal window,
the event logs can be filtered.</stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the bottom of the UPS Tuner window, click <uicontrol>Event Log Viewer</uicontrol>.</p>
            <stepxmp>The event logs can now be filtered by module, date, event
type or event description for an easy overview of a single alarm.<p/>
               <p/>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
      </ol>
